'''Agha Iqrar Haroon''' ({{lang-ur|آغا اقرار ہارون}} ({{lang-ru|Ага АКрар Харун}} ; born August 16, 1965) is a [[People of Pakistan|Pakistani]] research journalist and political analyst. He started his career in 1986. Since then, he has been working on different assignments with different international television channels and newspapers including ETN News agency Islamabad, Al-Jazeera Television Islamabad, Abdu Dubai Television Islamabad, Chief Control News Waqt Television Lahore, and Geo News Lahore. He appears as regional expert on different television channels of Pakistan including state run television PTV News.
Haroon worked with different media houses such as Nawa - i - Waqt Group, Al-Jazeera Television Channel in Pakistan, Abu Dhabi TV, Waqt TV, GEO News, and Abb Takk. He is currently as Foreign Affairs expert at state run television PTV News and Chief Editor of English and Russian news agency Dispatch News Desk. Haroon is a Research Scholar of Eurasian Studies and has been teaching in Central Asia and South Asia.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ecoclub.com/headlines/interviews/all-interviews/731-111019-iqrar-haroon|title=Interview: Agha Iqrar Haroon, Honorary Head, The Region Initiative (TRI), Pakistan|last=Petropoulos|first=Antonis|date=|work=ecoclub.com|access-date=2018-10-27|language=en-gb}}</ref> He has written a number of research papers about development in Eurasia. Haroon won an International Award for his journalistic work in Central Asia.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pressreader.com/pakistan/pakistan-today-karachi/20151009/281578059492021/TextView|archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20151208121409/https://www.pressreader.com/pakistan/pakistan-today-karachi/20151009/281578059492021/TextView|archive-date=8 December 2015|dead-url=yes|title=Kazakhstan awards Pakistani journalist|date=9 October 2015|website=Press Reader|publisher=Pakistan Today (Karachi)}}</ref> He has received the Award of Excellence from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Government of Kazakhstan.<ref>{{cite web |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208152327/http://www.app.com.pk/en_/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=362594&Itemid=2|archive-date=8 December 2015|url=http://www.app.com.pk/en_/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=362594&Itemid=2|title=Kazakhstan awards Pakistani journalist|date=9 October 2015|publisher=Associated Press of Pakistan}}</ref>
==Early life== Born in 1965, Haroon grew up in [[Lahore]]. He is a grandson of [[Hifz-ur-Rehman]] who was a Pakistani archaeologist, historian and linguist and son of Abdul Aziz, managing proprietor of the newspaper Paisa Akhbaar.{{citation needed|date=October 2018}}
